2026-04-18 | Mirror Distance of an Integer

	Question
Return the mirror distance of n.

	Approach
1.	Reverse the number:
		extract digits one by one  

2.	Compute:
		abs(n - reversedNumber)  

	Time Complexity
	O(digits)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int reverseNum(int x){
        int rev = 0;
        while(x > 0){
            rev = rev * 10 + x % 10;
            x /= 10;
        }
        return rev;
    }

    int mirrorDistance(int n) {
        int rev = reverseNum(n);
        return abs(n - rev);
    }
};

	Key Insight
This is a simple **digit manipulation problem**:
- reverse number  
- compute absolute difference  

Leading zeros automatically disappear during reversal.
